import java.sql.Timestamp
import de.qaware.mlwb.api._
import org.apache.spark.sql.Encoders
start: java.sql.Timestamp = 2014-11-29 00:00:00.0
end: java.sql.Timestamp = 2015-10-03 00:00:00.0
defined object Context
inRange: (c: de.qaware.mlwb.api.Counter)Boolean

paragraphs.text:
%spark
import org.apache.spark.sql.Encoders
import de.qaware.mlwb.featureextractor._

constantNames
    .map(Parser.parseString(_)) (Encoders.bean(classOf[LinearizedMetric]))
    .groupByKey(new PropertyKey(_)) (Encoders.bean(classOf[PropertyKey]))
    .mapValues(_.getPropertyValueTuple) (Encoders.bean(classOf[Tuple]))
    .mapGroups((k, values) => new PartlyLinearizedMetric(k, values.toArray.distinct.sorted (Ordering.by[Tuple, String](t => t.getArr.mkString(","))))) (Encoders.bean(classOf[PartlyLinearizedMetric]))
    .groupByKey(_.getValueSet) (Encoders.bean(classOf[ValueSet]))
    .mapValues(_.getPropertyKey.getName)
    .mapGroups((vs, pks) => new DeLinearizedMetric(vs, pks.toArray.distinct.sorted)) (Encoders.bean(classOf[DeLinearizedMetric]))
    .collect.foreach(e => {
        println("#")
        println("names:           [" + e.getProperties.mkString(", ") + "]")
        println("with properties: " + e.getValueSet.getKeyTuple.getArr.mkString(", "))
        println("values:          " + ("*" * e.getValueSet.getKeyTuple.getArr.mkString(", ").length))
        e.getValueSet.getValues.foreach(v => println("                 " + v.getArr.mkString(",")))
        println("#")
    })
// .take/.takeRight/.slice if too big

%spark
import collection.JavaConverters._
import de.qaware.mlwb.impl.sparksolr.MetricsServiceImpl
import scala.collection.mutable.ListBuffer

def restarts(c: Counter): List[Timestamp] = {
    val vps = c.getValuePoints
    
    var result = new ListBuffer[Timestamp]
    var lastUptime = vps.get(0).getValue
    for (i <- 1 until vps.size) {
        val elem = vps.get(i)
        if (elem.getValue != -1) {
            if (elem.getValue < lastUptime) {
                result += elem.getDate
            }
            lastUptime = elem.getValue
        }
    }
    
    result.toList
}

val service = new MetricsServiceImpl.Factory(sqlc).getInstance("192.168.1.100:2181", "ekgdata")
val query = new QueryMetricContext.Builder().withMetrics("*Runtime*Uptime*").withHost("lp*").withStart(start).withEnd(end).build()

val uptimeDS = service.getCounters(query, Granularity.NONE, AggregationType.AVG)

uptimeDS
    .flatMap(c => restarts(c).map(_.toString.substring(0, 15) + "0").map(ts => Tuple2(ts, Tuple2(c.getMetric.getHost, c.getMetric.getProcs))).iterator)
    .groupByKey(_._1).mapGroups((timestamp, systems) => Tuple2(timestamp, systems.map(_._2).toArray.sorted))
    .collect
    .sortBy(x => x._1)
    .foreach(x => println(x._1 + " | " + x._2.mkString(", ")))
    
/*uptimeDS
    .flatMap(c => restarts(c).map(_.toString.substring(0, 10)).map(ts => Tuple2(ts, Tuple2(c.getMetric.getHost, c.getMetric.getProcs))).iterator)
    .groupByKey(_._1).mapGroups((timestamp, systems) => Tuple2(timestamp, systems.map(_._2).toArray.sorted))
    .collect
    .sortBy(x => x._1)
    .foreach(x => println(x._1 + " 00:00:01" + " & " + x._2.size + " \\\\"))*/
